Defendant John  Odom in court, in custody, with attorney Katie Beth Bricco.   Ted S. Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 and 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:

COUNT 1
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

9 Months STRAIGHT TIME 

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Be involved in AA/NA and obtain a sponsor;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Obtain a valid license within the first 6 months;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment within 45 days;

Costs: $253.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00


COUNT 2

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

90 Days STRAIGHT TIME  CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1

Term of Probation: 2 Years  CONCURRENT TO 1

Conditions of Probation:  SAME AS COUNT 1

Costs: $243.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00


Costs and Surcharges to to be paid as a condition of probationat the rate of $75.00  per month commencing 11-1-14; alternate 90 hours of community service.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.
